  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\nWhen gas limit is not 21000 (instead of 21000 it is 26853), it is possible when recipient address is a contract, at attempt to use \"Set max\" function it throws \"Not enough eth for gas\" error.\nNot sure it is a common case, also not sure what applications are using contract address as deposit option for ETH.\n\n#### Expected behavior\ncan use \"Set max\"\n\n#### Actual behavior\n\n\n\n### Reproduction\n\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\n\n- Open Status\n- Open wallet, tap on \"Send\"\n- Paste `0x881d40237659c251811cec9c364ef91dc08d300c`\n\n### Additional Information\n\n- Status version: nightly 20/11/20\n- Operating System: Android, iOS",
